1) Common Features (in menubar)
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
1.1) File menu
1.1.1) Open map - opens antoher (already existing map) in this window. 
1.1.2) New map - opens a new map in a new window (in edit mode).
1.1.3) new Window - opens a new window with the same map.
                    (history not preserved)
1.1.4) Edit
1.1.5) Browse
1.1.6) Print
1.1.7) Close
1.1.8) Exit

1.2) Settings menu
1.2.1) Resolver tables - Displays the lookup tables (for editing).
1.2.2) Language Menu - change language
1.2.3) Zoom Menu - zoom the map.
1.2.4) Set as startmap - sets the current map as startmap.

1.3) Tools menu
1.3.1) Component editor - views the editor where the 'non visual'
                          aspects of components can be edited 
1.3.2) Reload all - reloads the components from storage.

1.4) Help menu
1.4.1) help - opens the help map (from the network)
1.4.2) about - opens the about map (from the local resources)


2) Browse mode:
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
2.1) In the popupmenu over a neuron.
2.1.1) Surf - change map to the detailed or a context neighbourhood map.
2.1.2) View - lists the content for this neuron in the
            contentlistdisplayer.
2.1.3) Info - Views the metadata (on this neuron or map) in the 
              metaDataDisplayer.
2.1.4) Copy - referenes the map (in background) or neuron (over box or
              axon) to the clipboard.
2.1.5) Edit - opens the componentEditor with the abstract information 
            for the neuron or map displayed.

3) Edit mode:
^^^^^^^^^^^^^
3.1) Map menu - right click in background 
3.1.1) Edit map - opens the ComponentEditor with this map displayed.
3.1.2) Insert Neuron menu - inserts a neuron where you clicked.
3.1.2.1) with URI - give absolute or relative path to a neuron. 
3.1.2.2) from clipboard - insert visual representation of neuron
                          reffered to in clipoard.
3.1.3) Create menu - hierarchical menus containing neurontypes,
                     determining created neurons apperance etc.
3.1.4) Copy - reference this map in clipboard.

3.2) Neuron box menu - 
3.2.1) Edit Neuron - opens the componenteditor with this neuron
                     displayed.
3.2.2) Remove Neuron - Removes the graphical representation of the
                       neuron in this map, neuron isn't removed 
                       from storage though. 
3.2.3) Show axon - axons not displayed in this map are displayed 
3.2.4) Create axons - adds axons to the current neuron.
3.2.5) Content - A menu, adds content to this neuron.
3.2.5.1) Create - creates a new content and adds it to this neuron
3.2.5.2) from Clipboard - inserts a content from clipboard
3.2.6) Toggle box visible - displays or hides the box for this neuron.
3.2.7) Toggle neuronline visible - displays or hides the neuronline.
3.2.8) Edit detailedmap - A popup where you can change the 
                           detailedmap on this neuron in this map.
3.2.9) view - as in (2.1.2)
3.2.10) info - as in (2.1.3)
3.2.11) copy - as in (2.1.4)

3.3) Neuron axon menu - right click on neuron box.
3.2.1) Edit Neuron - as in (3.2.1)
3.2.2) Remove Neuron - as in (3.2.2)
3.2.3) Show axon - as in (3.2.3)
3.2.4) Hide axon - removes the graphical representation of the axon
                   in this map, axon isn't removed from neuron.
3.2.5) Create axons - as in (3.2.4)
3.2.6) Remove axon - axons is removed from neuron, and with it
                     it's graphical representation in this map.
                     (Representations in other maps has to be 
                      explicitly removed (displayed in red)).
3.2.7) Content - as in (3.2.5)
3.2.8) Toggle box visible - as in (3.2.6)
3.2.9) Toggle neuronline visible - as in (3.2.7)
3.2.10) Edit detailedmap - as in (3.2.8)
3.2.11) view - as in (2.1.2)
3.2.12) info - as in (2.1.3)
3.2.13) copy - as in (2.1.4)

4) Content selector  (invoked from 2.1.2 and other similiar)
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
4.1) Content menu - invoked on right press over content
4.1.1) View - displays the choosen content in Content Displayer (ex: a
              browser)
4.1.2) Info - displays the metadata about the content in the
              metadatadisplayer
4.1.3) Copy - Makes a refference in the clipboard (allows (3.2.5.2))
4.1.4) Edit - opens the componentEditor with the abstract information 
              for the choosen content.






